<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,978,1867]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1771,1795]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
It is noteworthy that more adult than juvenile specimens of this genus were collected during November–December, 2009 from Xishuangbanna. The species 
<taxonomicName authority="Ono, 2002" authorityName="Ono" authorityYear="2002" box="[866,1198,1806,1830]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Synaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nangoku">
<emphasis box="[866,1071,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Synaema nangoku</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, H." box="[1079,1198,1806,1830]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="201 - 210" refId="ref43210" refString="Ono, H. (2002) New species of crab spiders (Araneae, Thomisidae) from Japan. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Series A (Zoology), 28, 201 - 210." type="journal article" year="2002">Ono, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1268,1332,1807,1830]" name="Japan" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Japan</collectingCountry>
could be a member of this genus judging by the illustrations (
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, H." box="[735,853,1842,1866]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="201 - 210" refId="ref43210" refString="Ono, H. (2002) New species of crab spiders (Araneae, Thomisidae) from Japan. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Series A (Zoology), 28, 201 - 210." type="journal article" year="2002">Ono 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
